            <div class="portfolio-title">
                <h3><a href="https://www.responsibly.me">Responsibly.me</a></h3>
            </div>
            <div class="portfolio-text">
                <p>Responsibly.me is a web platform for consumers to make more socially responsible purchasing decisions. Responsibly.me aggregates existing rankings on a company’s Corporate Social Responsibility initiatives and recommends similar products from brands with higher grades. Responsibly.me also provides a dashboard for users to understand their social responsibility values and purchasing habits in order to encourage them to shop more consciously.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="portfolio-image">
                <img src="/assets/responsibly/homepage.png" alt="Responsibly.me Homepage"></img>
            </div>
            <div class="portfolio-text">
                <p>In this current climate where we face a growing number of wicked problems, both the public and private sector need to do more to create a better world for all of us. According to the 2017 Cone Communications CSR study, 63% of Americans are hopeful businesses will take the lead to drive social and environmental change moving forward. This number increases to 71% for millennials and younger generations. But are these companies doing enough?</p>
                <p>Companies have instituted CSR initiatives for some time now, but they have largely been in the service of raising the value of their corporate brand. Third-party organizations like the Corporate Knights and Greenpeace analyze and grade these CSR efforts, and yet only 39% of consumers “researched a company’s business practices or support of social and environmental issues” (2017 Cone Communications CSR study). The majority of users simply are not aware of the efforts corporations take to tackle these social issues. Given that around 90% of consumers say they would trust a company more if that company supports a social/environmental cause, why aren’t companies doing more to get the word out there on their efforts?</p>
                <p>Responsibly.me aims to make these efforts more transparent and easier to access for regular consumers. I have collected data on 50 of the top 100 brands according to Forbes and have built a web extension in which users can learn about a brand’s social responsibility rankings. I have also created design wireframes for product recommendations and the user dashboard to get an idea of where I hope to take this project.</p>
            </div>
