            <div class="portfolio-title">
                <h3>User Testing</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="portfolio-text">
                <p>So far, I have user-tested my platform with industry experts as well as fellow ITPers. Things I’ve learned:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>A lot of people like the idea and can see the value it can have in the space. This was especially encouraging coming from those in the social impact space. </li>
                    <li>Users don’t need a lot of credibility. They just need a box to check off that lets them know that their choice is good. Give them that option and let them go down the rabbit hole if they want. </li>
                    <li>Users want to participate. They want to see how they are doing. How can we keep shoppers engaged? </li>
                    <li>Users like the Chrome Extension experience. Continue to make it as non-intrusive as possible. </li>
                    <li>Users want to get to the products that do good. Explore gamifying this action. </li>
                    <li>Stats don’t mean much to some people, but mean a lot to others. Information means more. Explore making the stats engaging and real for users. But leave an option for users to go down rabbit holes to find the data they are interested in.</li>
                    <li>Competitor information is the most relevant for users. Low scores are particularly influential.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
